![122.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1586986556415-EI6OJYD0EE5KK4XGF6WS/122.jpg)

The Marvel Cinematic Universe as it stands is an extraordinary achievement in the history of cinema. Still, even with 23 films under its belt, not all of them are critically acclaimed. On this episode, the guys resurrect a **Major Issues** tradition of Which Was Worse where they pit two critically panned comic book films against one another to decide...**Which Was Worse**! Its WWW MCU edition as **_Thor: The Dark World_** faces off against **_Incredible Hulk_**! Its Hemsworth Vs Norton, Dark Elves Vs Abominations and Thunderbolts vs Gods of Thunder in this passion-filled, heart-stopping battle for the ages!  
  
If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](/comicbookclique/episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
